AB  - The proceedings contain 54 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Natural Language and Information Systems. The topics include: Accelerating End-to-End PDF to Markdown Conversion Through Assisted Generation; Comparison of Pipelines, Seq2seq Models, and LLMs for Rare Disease Information Extraction; a Multiple Graphical Convolution Networks Approach for Aspect-Based Sentiment Classification; how Important is Domain-Specific Language Model Pretraining and Instruction Finetuning for Biomedical Relation Extraction?; ShortPathQA: A Dataset for Controllable Fusion of Large Language Models with Knowledge Graphs; explaining Bias in Internal Representations of Large Language Models via Concept Activation Vectors; duplicate Bug Report Retrieval for New Bug Reports; Context is the Key for LLM-Based Text Segmentation; MultiProSE: A Multi-label Arabic Dataset for Propaganda, Sentiment, and Emotion Detection; CLIP-Driven Deep Hashing for Cross-Modal Retrieval; WIP: Iterative Post-training Pruning with Weighted Importance Estimation for Large Language Models; A Comparative Study on the Development of a Thai Legal QA Framework Using Large Language Models and Mixed Legal Datasets; Leveraging Generative AI for Chronic Kidney Disease Prediction: A Comparative Study of Open-Source LLMs; LADDER: Latent Attention and Decomposition for Deep Enhanced Retrieval in Medical Question-Answering Systems; test It Before You Trust It: Applying Software Testing for Trustworthy In-Context Learning; CAFE: Context-Aware Applicability-Weighted Fairness Evaluation; A Survey of LoRA Algorithm Variations for Language Models; ViMRHP: A Vietnamese Benchmark Dataset for Multimodal Review Helpfulness Prediction via Human-AI Collaborative Annotation; towards an Ontological Approach to Browser Fingerprinting Detection and Privacy Risk Assessment; dual-Style Transcription of Historical Manuscripts Based on Multimodal Small Language Models with Switchable Adapters; semantic Reasoning for Device Identification in Dynamic Internet of Things Environments with Large Language Models; Instruction Tuning TextFlow Semi-automatic RFCs Generation; news Timeline Summarization: Recent Methods; QA2HALL: A Framework for Generating Non-trivial Hallucination Detection Datasets from KGQA Datasets.
