TY  - CONF
TI  - Clay play: A metaphorical LLM interface for dynamic idea generation and exploration
AU  - Aikawa, Y.
AU  - Bae, J.
AU  - Misaki, D.
AB  - We propose Idea Clay, a direct manipulation interface for large language models (LLMs) designed to support non-linear and continuous idea generation. Inspired by the metaphor of clay play, users interact with visual “idea fragments” by merging and splitting them to invoke LLM-driven operations. The objective of this research is to facilitate the iterative and exploratory nature of divergent thinking through metaphor-based manipulations, thereby supporting the generation of creative ideas. A user study with 12 participants provided evidence that the interaction of clay metaphors facilitates intuitive and efficient generation and exploration, thereby promoting the creative process. We discuss how metaphor-based manipulation can promote intuitive and engaging human-AI collaboration in creative tasks. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).
