TY  - CONF
TI  - Transforming hallucinations into discovery: A neurosymbolic framework for human-AI collaborative knowledge evolution
AU  - Monti, M.
AU  - Magaña-Vsevolodovna, R.I.
T2  - Frontiers in Artificial Intelligence and Applications
AB  - Large Language Model (LLM)”hallucinations” can be catalysts for discovery. This paper introduces a neurosymbolic framework leveraging these errors to enhance reliability and interdisciplinary innovation. We propose an ontology-guided verification and human-in-the-loop (HITL) refinement cycle, where LLM-generated insights are checked against and refine an evolving ontology. Discrepancies are flagged, and experts validate and integrate these insights, mitigating biases and fostering emergent concepts. A case study in avionic diagnostics demonstrates potential. Our contributions include a framework for leveraging LLM hallucinations, suggesting pathways towards improved scalability, fostering interdisciplinary insights, and ensuring ethical alignment, contributing to Hybrid Human-AI Intelligence. Future work will focus on implementation and validation. © 2025 The Authors.
