TY  - CONF
TI  - Generative AI-based real-time drowsiness detection and alert system for enhanced driver safety
AU  - Gowda, D.M.
AU  - Mallikarjun H, M.
AU  - Ramesh, M.
AB  - This paper presents a novel driver safety and assistance system that seamlessly integrates real-time monitoring with artificial intelligence (AI) to enhance road safety, minimize fatigue-related incidents, and improve the overall driving experience. The core functionality of the system lies in its ability to detect signs of drowsiness by continuously analyzing live camera feeds for two key facial indicators: yawning and drowsiness. These visual cues are monitored with high accuracy to identify early stages of driver fatigue, and when such conditions are detected, the system promptly issues proactive safety alerts to help prevent potential accidents. In addition to visual analysis, the system incorporates a multilingual speech recognition module that supports over 26 languages, enabling drivers from diverse backgrounds to interact naturally with an AI assistant through voice commands. The assistant aids in location-based services, such as finding nearby gas stations, restaurants, or hospitals, and also responds to general queries-effectively reducing driver distraction and cognitive load. The system's looped architecture ensures persistent, real-time monitoring while staying responsive to user commands, supported by a dedicated exit mechanism that grants drivers full control over system engagement. This human-in-the-loop approach balances automated oversight with user autonomy, distinguishing it from rigid, traditional Advanced Driver Assistance Systems (ADAS). The modular architecture also supports future upgrades, including cloud-based services, driver behavior profiling, and personalized features. Trained on diverse datasets, the algorithms offer reliable performance across different lighting conditions and driver demographics. Preliminary testing demonstrates improved driver responsiveness, alertness, and satisfaction, making this system a promising advancement in intelligent and inclusive automotive safety technologies. © 2025 IEEE.
