TY  - CONF
TI  - LLM-MAC: LLM-driven multi-agent coordination for generalizable home energy management
AU  - Yang, Y.
AU  - Yang, Q.
AU  - Li, D.
AU  - Sun, L.
AU  - Sen, L.
AU  - Liu, R.
T2  - Chinese Control Conference, CCC
AB  - Home Energy Management (HEM) is essential for optimizing residential electricity consumption, reducing costs, and integrating distributed energy resources. Existing methods, including rule-based, optimization-based, and RL-based approaches, struggle to balance adaptability, computational efficiency, and explainability. This study proposes LLM-MAC, a novel LLM-driven multi-agent coordination framework that enables zero-shot energy scheduling without task-specific training. The framework employs a hierarchical agent structure, where Agent1 defines constraints, Agent2 optimizes scheduling, and Agent3 resolves conflicts iteratively. Experiments on diverse household configurations demonstrate that LLM-MAC effectively generates feasible, cost-efficient, and interpretable scheduling strategies, outperforming traditional methods in adaptability and real-time execution. The results highlight the potential of LLMs in enhancing HEM, bridging the gap between flexibility and computational efficiency while supporting human-in-the-loop optimization. © 2025 Technical Committee on Control Theory, Chinese Association of Automation.
