TY  - CONF
TI  - mdok of KInIT: Robustly fine-tuned LLM for binary and multiclass AI-generated text detection
AU  - Macko, D.
T2  - CEUR Workshop Proceedings
AB  - The large language models (LLMs) are able to generate high-quality texts in multiple languages. Such texts are often not recognizable by humans as generated, and therefore present a potential of LLMs for misuse (e.g., plagiarism, spams, disinformation spreading). An automated detection is able to assist humans to indicate the machine-generated texts; however, its robustness to out-of-distribution data is still challenging. This notebook describes our mdok approach in robust detection, based on fine-tuning smaller LLMs for text classification. It is applied to both subtasks of Voight-Kampff Generative AI Detection 2025, providing remarkable performance (1st rank) in both, the binary detection as well as the multiclass classification of various cases of human-AI collaboration. © 2025 Copyright for this paper by its authors.
