AB  - Large language models (LLMs) understand human user requests and generate plausible responses. However, generic LLMs usually lack the capability to derive task plans with executable actions for robots in real-world scenarios. This review highlights prompt engineering and explores the current literature on integrating LLMs into pick-and-place robots. The results include state-of-the-art requirements, a framework to enhance robotics with LLMs through prompt engineering, and the identification of research gaps and key research areas for implementation. © The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Switzerland AG 2025.
