TI  - 2nd european symposium on artificial intelligence in manufacturing, ESAIM 2024
T2  - Lecture Notes in Mechanical Engineering
AB  - The proceedings contain 29 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Artificial Intelligence in Manufacturing. The topics include: On the Use of Generative AI to Support In-Line Process Monitoring in Zero-Defect Manufacturing; Laser Metal Deposition (LMD) Process Monitoring: From 3D Visualization of Sensor Data Towards Anomaly Detection; an Explainable Active Learning Approach for Enhanced Defect Detection in Manufacturing; Synthetic Data for AI-Powered Ultrafast Laser Based Micro-structuring Method Description; Towards Explicable AI in Systemic Identification of Surrogate Models of Manufacturing Processes; Leveraging Generative AI for Synthetic Data Generation: Improving 6-DOF Pose Estimation in Assembly Systems; CPPM Copilot: Proposing an AI-Based Assistant for Manual Assembly Tasks in a Flexible Production; generalized Authoring Tool for Computer Vision Machine Learning Application Deployments; collaborative Learning in Shared Production Environment Using Federated Image Classification; An OPIS-Based Knowledge Engineering Framework for Collaborative Robotics; a Tool for Generating and Labelling Domain Randomised Synthetic Images for Object Recognition in Manufacturing; human-Robot Interaction Through Egocentric Hand Gesture Recognition; advanced Computer Vision for Industrial Safety: Indoor Human Worker Localization Using Deep Learning; LOS Data Set: A Large Scale Online Scheduling Benchmark for Flexible Job Shop Problems with Setup and Transportation Times; agent-Based Communication for Fault Diagnosis in Skill-Based Production Environments Using Messages Based on I4.0 Language and Asset Administration Shells; Decision Support System (DSS) for Manufacturing Engineering of Cans Rolling; AI Based Solutions for Manufacturing Mass Customization; Industrial Maintenance Optimization Based on the Integration of Large Language Models (LLM) and Augmented Reality (AR); On an AI-Based System Architecture to Generate Robotic Cells in VR Environments; Building on the Principles of LLM Models: Vector-Based Anomaly Detection in Pneumatic Cylinder Systems.
