AB  - We present an innovative augmented reality game which aims to demonstrate a new dimension of interaction between humans and large language models through non-verbal gesture-based communication. Players collaborate with an LLM-controlled avatar to identify and correct discrepancies in an augmented reality environment, relying solely on non-verbal cues. The game aims to explore the emergence and evolution of pragmatic communication between humans and AI agents. © 2024 The Authors.
