AB  - Drama script generation is a challenging yet valuable task with applications in film, gaming, and digital storytelling. Current LLM- and agent-based methods achieve some narrative coherence but often suffer from content homogenization, limited creativity, and underdefined human roles. To address these issues, we propose Co-DIRECT, a human–AI co-creation framework that positions a human director as a central collaborator in a Director-in-the-Loop (DiL) paradigm and employs a multi-agent structure: a Writer Agent constructs narrative arcs, an Actor Agent performs context-aware dialogues, and a Critic Agent evaluates consistency and emotional expressiveness. An ontology-driven knowledge graph extracts narratological principles from classical scripts to guide plot development and iterative refinement. Extensive evaluations show that Co-DIRECT outperforms strong baselines in narrative coherence, emotional depth, content diversity, and script structure. These results highlight the benefits of combining narratological knowledge, multi-agent collaboration, and DiL human guidance for controllable and creative script generation.
