AB  - Oral cancer presents significant challenges for healthcare professionals worldwide in terms of diagnosis and treatment. Recent advances in artificial intelligence (AI) offer new opportunities to enhance patient care and outcomes. This paper explores the feasibility of integrating ChatGPT, an AI language model, into clinical practice to improve analysis, therapy, and support for patients with oral cancer. By utilizing ChatGPT's natural language processing and information synthesis capabilities, healthcare practitioners can enhance decision-making, personalize patient treatment, and improve patient education and support. However, it is crucial to address concerns related to data protection, ethical considerations, and technological limitations to ensure the responsible incorporation of ChatGPT into oral cancer treatment. Collaboration between healthcare providers, researchers, and AI developers holds the potential to revolutionize oral cancer care.
