AB  - Interpreting deep learning predictions in financial markets remains a central challenge, as temporal dependencies and inter-stock relations often obscure model reasoning. This paper introduces a unified framework that combines Temporal Graph Convolutional Network for stPGExpla for grapLarge Language Models (LLMs) such as GPT-4o and LLaMA3 to translate structural explanations into natural-language financial reports. Experiments on the S&P 100 and NASDAQ-100 benchmarks show that TGCNs capture spatiotemporal dependencies effectively, achieving test accuracies of 58.9% and 50.6%, respectively. To assess explanation quality, we propose a factual sensitivity protocol and find that GPT-4o generates the most consistent and context-sensitive reports. While predictive accuracy remains moderate due to market volatility, the primary contribution lies in improving model transparency and accessibility, bridging complex GNN outputs with human-readable narratives. The study also outlines directions for future work, including real-time deployment and user-in-the-loop evaluation to better align explainable AI with financial practice.
