AB  - Government citizen hotlines are essential for addressing diverse public inquiries, but conventional dispatch systems face challenges including inefficient knowledge extraction, limited integration of knowledge graph (KG) and large language model (LLM), and poor adaptation to domain-specific contexts. This study introduces a collaborative enhancement framework that synergizes KG and LLM to improve the accuracy and efficiency of hotline dispatch operations. The proposed method employs automated knowledge extraction through prompt engineering, robust multi-source validation and fusion techniques, and a bidirectional KG-LLM enhancement loop to ensure dynamic knowledge optimization. By incorporating multimodal data processing and a self-optimizing closed-loop mechanism, the framework enhances knowledge coverage, mitigates model hallucinations, and accelerates response times. Experimental results in real-world citizen hotline scenarios demonstrate significant improvements in dispatch accuracy and operational efficiency over baseline approaches, underscoring its transformative potential for intelligent government service delivery.
