AB  - Microelectronics education requires hands-on training in semiconductor fabrication, cleanroom procedures, and hardware assembly, but traditional methods can be costly and resource-intensive. This paper presents an AI-driven immersive training and assessment system designed to enhance microelectronics and VLSI education using digital twins and extended reality (XR). Our system automatically generates interactive training modules from expert demonstration videos and instructional materials, leveraging Large Language Models (LLMs) for instructional content extraction and real-time assessment. The platform provides adaptive guidance, dynamically adjusting difficulty levels based on trainee performance, while an integrated human-in-the-loop system allows teachers to refine grading criteria. Additionally, to give the real time feedback to students, we also allow the teacher to join remotely as preceptor. We demonstrate the effectiveness of our system through a case study in semiconductor fabrication training, showcasing its potential for university curricula and industry workforce development. By reducing the reliance on expensive physical labs and providing scalable, self-paced learning experiences, this approach offers a novel and cost-effective solution for microelectronics education.
