AB  - Short and ambiguous queries in chat interfaces like Microsoft Copilot often lead to vague or irrelevant LLM responses, increasing task completion time. Hence, we introduce a novel problem: semi-automatically enhancing such queries/prompts into specific, well-formed ones with clear intent. Unlike prompt optimization, our approach adds relevant sub-intents or constraints rather than just rewording for brevity. We propose EnhanceMyPrompt, which uses small language models (SLMs) to enrich prompts by adding sub-intents/constraints, suggesting placeholders, and recommending popular values. We also introduce metrics to measure prompt improvement, user effort, and LLM response quality. Experiments on a proprietary Microsoft Copilot and LMSYS+NQ datasets with four SLMs show effectiveness: EnhanceMyPrompt predicts user intents up to 3 turns ahead in  23
