AB  - With the rise of digital communication, phishing has emerged as the predominant cybercrime. Automated detection systems encounter challenges such as user trust issues and false positives, while human-centric solutions are resource-intensive and struggle with sophisticated attacks. Despite this threat, research on empowering users with automatic anti-phishing systems remains limited. This paper introduces a human-centric framework that utilizing Large Language Models (LLMs) to extract phishing indicators and generate meaningful warnings.Recognizing that certain information is unique to users, our system integrates user insights into anti-phishing measures. Preliminary results demonstrate the promise of LLM-driven approaches in crafting meaningful warnings, highlighting the synergy between human insight and machine intelligence in combating phishing. Our framework achieves over 80
