AU  - Zhan, ZeHui
AU  - Liang, ShiSong
T3  - Icdel '24
AB  - In the context of global educational reforms, interdisciplinary teaching has become a key concern in international education. Post the release of China's "Compulsory Education Curriculum Plan and Curriculum Standards (2022 Edition)," there's a pressing need to enhance interdisciplinary instruction, which poses challenges due to the extensive training required for teachers. This study investigates how Large Language Models (LLMs) like GPT-4 can assist in interdisciplinary instructional design. Using the new standards and the "C-POTE" model, researchers developed an AI Agent-based system called Inter-Agent for optimizing instructional design. The study shows that the Inter-Agent system can effectively refine teaching designs' core elements and offer innovative enhancements while maintaining the integrity of the original concepts.
