TY  - CONF
TI  - Survey of emerging trends in LLM agent benchmarking
AU  - Cao, Danyang
AU  - Yu, Ben
T3  - Bdnndl '25
AB  - As LLMs evolve into agents that can call tools and interact with environments, static benchmarks no longer reflect practical performance in realistic environments. This paper surveys current benchmarks and proposes a four-stage framework—generation, execution, evaluation, and compliance—that maps existing studies onto capability, scenario, and system axes. Comparing OSWorld, AgentBench, TravelPlanner, etc. Four principal gaps are identified: limited task coverage, fragmented evaluation metrics, high reproduction costs, and misalignment with human values. This study outlines five remedies: lightweight standards, cross-domain dynamic generation, self-supervised + preference-based evaluation, continual-learning testing, and open governance, envisioning an evolvable, auditable, and accountable “universal safety checkpoint” for large-scale AGI deployment.
