AB  - Group decision-making support has been a longstanding research topic. Achieving productive consensus in organizations remains challenging, as it requires participants to engage in discussions with broad perspectives and flexible thinking, and to understand problems from multiple perspectives. We have developed technologies and systems that support awareness of diverse values and viewpoints, aiming to enhance the productivity of discussions. This paper presents a discussion agent based on large language models (LLMs) that intervenes in human discussions to stimulate participants by introducing new perspectives, ideas, or critiques, thereby promoting more productive discussion. The agent is designed to change its behavior according to assigned roles within the discussion. We experimentally examined the impact of the agent’s behavior on human discussions.
