AB  - Continuation writing assessment is often slow, inconsistent, and hard to scale in real classrooms. We present Continuation Wing 1.0, a DeepSeek-assisted platform that couples an interpretable scoring framework with targeted feedback generation for secondary-school continuation tasks. The scorer integrates semantic matching, grammatical error density, and discourse coherence to produce aligned sub-scores for Content, Language, and Coherence, along with an overall score; the feedback module triages issues with a random-forest classifier and delivers template-guided, actionable suggestions prioritized by impact. A lightweight prompt-tuning setup ensures classroom-level latency. On a balanced evaluation set, the system reaches QWK 0.81 (Content) and 0.79 (Language), approaching a stronger LLM baseline while running substantially faster (128 tok/s vs. 22 tok/s) and reducing feedback false positives to 12
